title: '"the adoption of the humble turnip and other root crops for fodder heralded a revolution in medieval agriculture. Not only are these more effective than grazing for fattening up livestock over the summer, but they also provide a reliable energy-rich feed throughout the winter."'
pid: 20cfda1f-e003-45da-a9ba-734aacec9e89
body: |2-
  Before their introduction, every late autumn medieval Europe witnessed the mass slaughter of livestock, as there was simply insufficient food to keep the animals from starving before spring.
